title: REALISTIC 737 COCKPIT! Full Crew Flight with ATC to Atlanta (VATSIM)

media:group.media:title: REALISTIC 737 COCKPIT! Full Crew Flight with ATC to Atlanta (VATSIM)
media:group.media:description:
My co-pilot Fabian and I fly from Chicago to Atlanta on the VATSIM network, ATC included.
- Merch: http://www.Airforceproud95.store
- Venue: http://www.extremeflightsimulation.com

Fabian is a certified flight instructor and an experienced 737 simulator pilot. Huge thank you to him for making this video possible.
- Follow Fabian on Instagram: https://www.instagram.com/thepilotfabian
- Fabian's YouTube channel: https://www.youtube.com/channel/UCbrvTq76zxSuPJyAUgYh7Xw

American Airlines flight 1691, Boeing 737-800 service from Chicago O'Hare Int'l Airport (KORD) to Atlanta Hartsfield-Jackson Int'l Airport (KATL) with near full air traffic control coverage on the VATSIM network. Cold and dark start up to engine shutdown in Prepar3d V4. Checklists are abbreviated and edited for time, don't attempt in real plane.

My Twitter: http://www.twitter.com/Airforceproud95
